> Looking for a super quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Super Quick Creamy Cajun Pork and Cauliflower Rice in just 15 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Heat a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the @Riced Cauliflower{250%grams}.

Cook until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once cooked, cover to keep warm until serving.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%grams}, @Sliced Mushrooms{120%grams} and @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break the mince up as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Creme Fraiche{75%grams}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water{75%milliliter}. Stir in a knob of @?butter{}.

Bring to the boil then simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the cauli rice between #bowls{}. Top with the Cajun pork. Enjoy!